{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GThreadPool"},{"type":"text","text":" struct represents a thread pool."}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol\/exclusive","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol\/func","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol\/maxThreads","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol\/numThreads","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol\/userData"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties"},{"title":"Instance Methods","generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol\/free(immediate:wait:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol\/getMaxThreads()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol\/getNumThreads()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol\/moveToFront(data:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol\/push(data:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol\/set(maxThreads:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol\/setSortFunction(func:userData:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol\/unprocessed()"]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Inherits From","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"kind":"relationships","type":"inheritsFrom"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef"],"title":"Conforming Types","kind":"relationships","type":"conformingTypes"}],"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ThreadPoolProtocol","kind":"identifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PointerWrapper","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A thread pool is useful when you wish to asynchronously fork out the execution of work","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and continue working in your own thread. If that will happen often, the overhead of starting","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and destroying a thread each time might be too high. In such cases reusing already started"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"threads seems like a good idea. And it indeed is, but implementing this can be tedious"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and error-prone."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Therefore GLib provides thread pools for your convenience. An added advantage is, that the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"threads can be shared between the different subsystems of your program, when they are using GLib.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a new thread pool, you use [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.new"},{"type":"text","text":"]."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It is destroyed by [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.free"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you want to execute a certain task within a thread pool, use [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.push"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To get the current number of running threads you call [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_num_threads"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To get the number of still unprocessed tasks you call [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.unprocessed"},{"type":"text","text":"]."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To control the maximum number of threads for a thread pool, you use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_max_threads"},{"type":"text","text":"]. and [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.set_max_threads"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Finally you can control the number of unused threads, that are kept alive by GLib for future use.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The current number can be fetched with [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_num_unused_threads"},{"type":"text","text":"]."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The maximum number can be controlled by [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_max_unused_threads"},{"text":"] and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.set_max_unused_threads","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]. All currently unused threads","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"can be stopped by calling [func"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.stop_unused_threads","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"code":"GThreadPool","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Alternatively, use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef"},{"text":" as a lighweight, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/threadpoolprotocol"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Protocol","externalID":"s:4GLib18ThreadPoolProtocolP","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ThreadPoolProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ThreadPoolProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"ThreadPoolProtocol","symbolKind":"protocol"},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/ThreadPool":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GThreadPool","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct represents a thread pool.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/threadpool","title":"ThreadPool","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/ThreadPoolProtocol/numThreads":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol\/numThreads","title":"numThreads","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"numThreads","kind":